$interpreted: Hutchinson: O, what chill and tender hand with softest strokes doth turn my heart to ice...
Hutchinson: ...and scatter'd cruelest white, do lovers most like snow cover the... ah... ah—A-choo!
Hutchinson: So... so cold...
Hanbei: You idiot, what're you reciting "Sir Landon" at a time like this for?
Hutchinson: I just want to know how it'd feel to be a nobleman... Achoo!
Sophie: I'm f-f-f-freezing out here... I hope Rune's doing okay...
Eidatyr: Goddamn it, I'm gonna kill Stefan! How could he just abandon Rune to Theodore? What the hell!
Hutchinson: Wait! Mr. Stefan's gone already!
Hanbei: And you were just yammering about killing him. How many times are we going to have to hold you back!!
Eidatyr: S*@#, how could he betray us!? Let go of me, I can barely breathe at just the thought of it!
Eidatyr: Talking all about how he'd take Rune to negotiate with the Saga clan mother. As soon as I heard it, I knew that Theodore was up to his old tricks again!
Ru-yi: S-Sophie... Eidatyr's so terrifying when she's mad. Has she really killed someone before...
Sophie: ...Haha, Eidatyr's just joking around~
Tindoiimu: But... I can't even imagine that the former regent of the Kingdom of the Sun would be hiding himself away in the north...
Eidatyr: Don't even think about! I'd sooner let my eyeballs freeze over than give him my shelter!
Sophie: All right all right, that's enough already.
Sophie: At least Stefan took us this far. And he gave us these, too, by way of apology~
Eidatyr: Hmph! He'd still be with us if he had an ounce of good faith in him.
Sophie: He said he had to stay in Westport. Otherwise, who'd be there to take charge when the monsters come attacking...
Ru-yi: Y-yeah, and Westport's being overrun with them, it's like they've flown here from the East!
Eidatyr: Lousy excuses! That rascal Stefan just wanted to save himself the bother. He must have dumped him someplace!
Sophie: E-even if that was the case, wouldn't he be doing it to keep Westport safe?
Eidatyr: ......
Eidatyr: He's not the saint you think he is...
Eidatyr: ...Forget it. At least there's somebody watching over the town.
Eidatyr: ...We should go. Sir Whatshisface hasn't a clue what he's got himself into. The North isn't just a heartless lover—a tyrant is more like it.
Eidatyr: ...I'm not the tender type, and I'm not going to wait up for any of you. If you can't keep up you'll just have to fend for yourselves.
Eidatyr: ...We're already within the Saga clan's domain now.
Eidatyr: Watch your step. The clan may have put their strictest taboos upon the ocean, but outsiders aren't far behind.
Tindoiimu: Stefan said the two of them had been gone for a while already. Do we really have a hope of catching them up...
Eidatyr: Tch, we don't have a choice. I have to stop him before he does something stupid.
Sophie: Who are you talking about? Rune?
Eidatyr: No. The Saga clan mother. I'm afraid Theodore and Rune might gang up on her.
Sophie: Rune would never hurt anyone... And he's got no reason to be helping Theodore, either!
Eidatyr: Who do you think it was who drove me out of Westport, who turned Stefan from my trusty second-in-command into a jumped-up head honcho?
Sophie: You mean...
Eidatyr: Whoever's left standing gets to call the shots, and I ain't standing anymore. If it weren't Theodore and Rune joining forces to take me down, then who else do you think it was?
Eidatyr: Rune isn't the person you thought you knew. He's Theodore's man now.
Sophie: I don't believe it...
Ru-yi: Ah! Sophie, maybe Rune never replied to all those letters you sent to Westport because—
Eidatyr: ...Would the Rune you knew ever let your letters go unanswered?
Sophie: ......
Tindoiimu: That lightbeam... Remember when we beat back the Monster of Judgment...!
Eidatyr: It's really made it out here to the north...!
Sophie: Wait, where are you going!?
Eidatyr: Don't ask dumb questions. I'm going after him, of course. He escaped last time, but I've still got some questions that need answering.
Sophie: Eh!?
Tindoiimu: I'm going with you.
Sophie: Tindoiimu too... Wait, you two!
Hutchinson: Uh... S-Sophie?
Sophie: Just a minute, Hutchinson, I've got my hands full—
Hanbei: Get your hands over here, why don't you!
Ru-yi: M-m-m-MONSTERS!
Eidatyr: Goddamn it, they've even made it out to the snow regions? Then those clans closer to the volcano must be—
Eidatyr: (...Don't do anything stupid, Valdrir, at least not until I get there!)
Eidatyr: Outta my way! Graaagh!
Tindoiimu: The snow... Is it getting heavier...?
Eidatyr: There's a blizzard on the way. It's not safe here. Move it!
